Configurar WebHook en GitHub para push de Build

```bash
oc describe bc python-basic -n admin-admin | grep -A5 "GitHub"
```
Obtener Secret de BC
```
oc get bc/python-basic -o yaml | grep -C 5 triggers
```

Extraer el secret

```
oc extract secret/java-app-github-webhook-secret --to=-
```
Validar que existe el clusterrole system:build-webhook
```bash
oc get clusterrole system:build-webhook
```
Si no existe, crearlo
```
cat <<'EOF' | oc apply -f -
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
kind: ClusterRole
metadata:
  name: system:build-webhook
rules:
- apiGroups:
  - build.openshift.io
  resources:
  - buildconfigs/webhooks
  verbs:
  - create
  - get
EOF
```
Vincular el clusterrole con el user system:anonymous
```
oc create clusterrolebinding system:build-webhook \
  --clusterrole=system:build-webhook \
  --user=system:anonymous
```

